nnis, whom Perry is trying to prevent from hacking into the Agency's mainframe. Meanwhile, Phineas and Ferb develop actual [[X-Ray Specs (novelty)|X-ray glasses]] after being ripped off by a novelty variety, and due to Perry's absence Dr. Doofenshmirtz appoints a [[houseplant|potted plant]] as his nemesis. Note: This episode is available on The Perry Files DVD along with the Spa Day episode.\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Phineas and Ferb (season 2)\n |LineColor = FFD700\n |Title = Spa Day\n |DirectedBy = Robert F. Hughes\n |WrittenBy= Aliki Theofilopoulos Grafft & Antoine Guilbaud\n |Aux2 = Jennifer Keene\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|11|2}}\n |ProdCode = 215b\n |Aux4 = <span style=\"color: grey;\"><small>N/A</small></span>\n |EpisodeNumber = 71\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 24\n |ShortSummary = Candace becomes sidetracked from a scheduled spa appointment and forces Stacey to work at a construction site with her because Jeremy is there, and the boys create their own spa to help make up for the missed appointment. Meanwhile, a stray cat Dr. Doofenshmirtz takes in as a pet causes chaos in his lab. Note: This episode is available on The Perry Files DVD along with the No More Bunny Business episode.\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Phineas and Ferb (season 2)\n |LineColor = FFD700\n |Title = [[Phineas and Ferb's Quantum Boogaloo]]\n |RTitle = {{Refn|group=nb|name=\"Halfhour\"}}\n |DirectedBy = Zac Moncrief\n |WrittenBy = Kaz & Kim Roberson \n |Aux2 = Scott Peterson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|11|9}}\n |ProdCode = 212\n |Aux4 = <span style=\"color: grey;\"><small>N/A</small></span>\n |EpisodeNumber = 72\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 25\n |ShortSummary = After encountering them in the future, an older version of Candace decides to steal Phineas and Ferb's time machine and go back in time to the day they [[Rollercoaster (Phineas and Ferb)|built a rollercoaster]] so she can help the present Candace catch them in the act. But when her actions cause a chain reaction turning the future into a [[dystopia]]n society led by Dr. Doofenshmirtz, the future Candace decides to enlist her present brothers to help restore the good future. \n\n''Guest stars'': [[Jennifer Stone]] as Amanda, [[Noah Munck]] as Xavier and [[Mois\u00e9s Arias]] as Fred\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Phineas and Ferb (season 2)\n |LineColor = FFD700\n |Title = [[List of Phineas and Ferb songs#Musical Cliptastic Countdown Season 1|Phineas and Ferb's Musical Cliptastic Countdown]]\n |RTitle = {{Refn|group=nb|name=\"Halfhour\"}}\n |DirectedBy = [[Dan Povenmire]]\n |WrittenBy = Scott Peterson (written)\n |Aux2 = Jon Colton Barry\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|11|16}}\n |ProdCode = 211\n |Aux4 = <span style=\"color: grey;\"><small>N/A</small></span>\n |EpisodeNumber = 73\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 26\n |ShortSummary = Major Monogram and Dr. Doofenshmirtz present a viewer-voted countdown of songs from Season 1, while Doofenshmirtz himself plots to take over the world with a song that is scientifically engineered to permanently become stuck in the mind.\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Phineas and Ferb (season 2)\n |LineColor = FFD700\n |Title = Bubble Boys\n |DirectedBy = Zac Moncrief\n |WrittenBy = J. G. Orrantia & Mike Roth\n |Aux2 = May Chan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|12|7}}\n |ProdCode = 216a\n |Aux4 = <span style=\"color: grey;\"><small>N/A</small></span>\n |EpisodeNumber = 74\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 27\n |ShortSummary = When Phineas and Ferb create the largest and most durble bubble ever, they, the Fireside Girls, Buford and Baljeet get trapped inside it flying around the city. Meanwhile, Candace practices driving and Dr. Doofenshmirtz uses a voice-altering cowboy hat to help him spread propaganda through country-and-western music.\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Phineas and Ferb (season 2)\n |LineColor = FFD700\n |Title = Isabella and the Temple of Sap\n |DirectedBy = Zac Moncrief\n |WrittenBy= J. G. Orrantia & Mike Roth\n |Aux2 = May Chan\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|1